# FactoryGame -- team

- When delegating or using "subagent": follow roles and startup prompts in **`AGENTS.md`** (repo root).
- Domain-specific skills and leads live in **`.cursor/skills/`** -- see **`AGENTS.md`** (components + `factory-game-integration-lead`, `factory-game-architect`, `factory-game-api-platform`). Subagents in **`.cursor/agents/`**. Activate with `@skill-name` or Task to subagent name.
- xUnit tests / broken tests: subagent **`factory-game-tester`** or `@factory-game-tester` (not the same as MCP `factory-game-playtester`).
- Game requirements: **`KRAVSPEC.md`** is the primary source of truth for behavior.
- **Git:** every commit message **must** contain **`Version`** from `Directory.Build.props` (mandatory; see **`factory-game-git-commit-push`**). Subagents must not commit without version prefix.

## Troubleshooting and running (owner environment)

- **Primary Azure Web App (dev):** `https://factorygame-h5hmbzgncnazcmgu.swedencentral-01.azurewebsites.net` -- same host for **PWA**, **`/v1` API**, **`/swagger`**, and (if enabled) **`GET /diagnostics/recent-logs`**.
- The **user** verifies in practice in **Azure** (no local `dotnet run` on the user's machine). **Do not ask** the user to start the app locally or open localhost to confirm behavior.
- **After the user tested in Azure:** the agent may fetch troubleshooting material from this base URL, e.g. **`GET /diagnostics/recent-logs`** (text, since process start). In **Production** app setting **`Diagnostics__ExposeRecentLogEndpoint` = `true`** must be set for the endpoint to respond; in **Development** it is always on. Alternative/complement: **App Service -> Log stream** / Application Insights if available.
- The **agent** runs **`dotnet build` / `dotnet test`** (and repo scripts such as Azure smoke when needed) **in the Cursor environment** -- that is the agent's local verification, not something the user needs to run.
